Sirius Invests $2.2 Billion to Titan Project, Interfax Says

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-09-07T08:32:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-07/sirius-invests-2-2-billion-to-titan-project-interfax-says.html
CHPP Sirius, a Ukrainian company
owned by Mykola Shcherbina, an adviser to former president
 Viktor Yushchenko , will invest $2.2 billion in exploring for
titanium in the Zhytomyr region,  Interfax-Ukraine  reported,
citing Serhiy Ryzhuk, the head of the Zhytomyr regional state
administration.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
